cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a method for multiple instance learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The method involves learning codebooks and using nearest neighbor voting for classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves image and video analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of density ratio models and histogram ratios suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of nearest neighbor voting suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
